reviews.review_text:
4.3 stars A tasty set list, including a very nice Crazy/Jam/High Time and a rocking Hell/Don't Ease closer in the first set, followed by a jam all the way through set 2, featuring a segue between Stranger & Eyes reminiscent of a China/Rider jam, a rollicking Love Light to make Pigpen proud and a very sweet Baby Blue second encore.

The playing is near tops all the way through, with just a few little rough spots hardly worth mentioning. 

The recording is good and has a lot of depth, with only a slight shade of tinniness and a slight lack of bass easily rectified with a good equalizer. There are currently 3 AUD recordings of this show, & this is my favorite.
